American rapper, record producer and fashion designer, Kanye West now known as Ye has enunciated a new idea to address the homeless crisis in Los Angeles. The rapper who is passionate about the course of helping the homeless in L.A recently revealed he wants the homeless to model his clothes in order to gain some modelling experience. This will involve them modelling for the upcoming Yezzy Collab with David Sabastian, the founder of Skid Row Fashion Week.   Feeding only thing on Nigerians’ mind, says Speed…     Whitemoney to hang out with Ojuelegba bridge co-tenants     TV actor Morgan Stevens found dead in kitchen   The duo met earlier this month while Ye was recording ‘Donda 2’ at his studio in L.A.’s Arts District near Skid Row and they decided to create a Yeezy X Skid Row Fashion Week clothing collab. - Advertisement - David noted his company donates a portion of all sales to helping those living on Skid Row and the factory that makes the clothes employs the homeless. In addition, the Yeezy collab will use 100% of the proceeds to help the homeless on Skid Row. The fashion line is slated to be launched on February 22, 2022, and the money from sales will help hire more people struggling with homelessness to work at the Skid Row Fashion Week factory.